shared_text:
Walter Guzman
September 10 at 6:13 AM ·

Meet Alissa Anderson who is the Site Bookkeeper (Account Clerk II) at San Jacinto High School (SJHS). Alissa has worked for SJHS for a little over a year and it's her first position at San Jacinto Unified School District (SJUSD). Alissa says: "My favorite part of working at SJHS is the team that I have the pleasure to be around. From ASB to the office staff to our fearless leader, everyone is so friendly and willing to help wherever is needed!"
She goes on to say: "I volunteer and love working in children's ministry, especially doing crafts and eating snacks :). I spent a year living in England right out of high school before going to college and love the culture and history there. My family and I love everything Disney and spend as much time at Disneyland/Disneyworld as we can! I have two sweet, silly kiddos (ages 2 and 6) and a wonderful husband of 10 years who has to be the most patient man alive!"

post_text: Another example of multi-generational San Jacinto Difference!
shared_text:
Hemet & San Jacinto Chronicle
June 19 at 1:09 PM ·

North Mountain’s “S” Shined for San Jacinto High’s Virtual Graduation

Throughout nearly the entire country, high school graduations were very different this year under the response to the COVID-19 pandemic. However, San Jacinto High School’s long-standing tradition of the “S” on North Mountain illuminating for 15 to 30 minutes at the close of commencement was still made possible by a group of alumni insisting that the tradition not miss a beat. “After surveying our students and parents on ceremony alternatives, we supported their desire to have a virtual graduation video released on June 4 at 7:30 p.m., the original scheduled day and time for the Class of 2020 commencement,” shared Principal Courtney Hall. “When the alumni agreed to light up the ‘S’ at the close of the video for us to live-stream, it really gave an extra touch in making it a real, although partial, graduation,” she noted.

Read more by clicking the link and search for (Virtual Graduation)
https://hsjchronicle.com/
#Education #SanJacinto

It helps the kids to be excited getting out for a drive and also calms parents’ concerns that we may not be able to find food for our children in the busy grocery stores. We appreciate everything that everyone at the district is doing for us!

Spring Forward- Its that time of the year again.

Daylight Savings Time begins this weekend! On Sunday, March 10th, clocks will spring forward one hour.

In addition to remembering to change your clocks, this is a great time to change the batteries in your smoke alarms. Saving your life can be as simple as checking your smoke alarms.

Enjoy the upcoming longer days!

shared_text:
Hemet Sheriff's Station
September 22, 2018 at 8:58 PM ·

Deputy Parsons, Deputy Dunlap, and Captain Purvis with actors Dan Lauria and Wendie Malick at the Idyllwild Arts Campus on September 22, 2018.

Wendy Malick and Dan Lauria starred in the play “The Guys.” “The Guys” tells the story of a New York City Fire Department captain (Lauria) who lost eight men in the collapse of the World Trade Center towers on Sept. 11. He is tasked with writing eulogies for the men’s memorial and Malick plays an editor who helps him with the writing.
